{
  "name": "OpenRecall Rules Audit",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "On-demand full rules audit. Walks the master rules in .kiro/steering/rules.md and checks the workspace for violations: spec traceability, threshold inlining, Pydantic v1 leakage, secret leakage, gitignore coverage, signature drift, and PBT seed.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run a full rules audit against .kiro/steering/rules.md. For each rule domain, report PASS/FAIL with evidence:\n\n1. RULE-SPEC: Confirm every modified file in the last commit cites an R or P ID in its commit message.\n2. RULE-CODE-04: grep incident_agent/ for inline threshold literals (0.85, 0.9). Only the named Final[float] constants in triage.py are allowed.\n3. RULE-CODE-02/03: grep for `from typing import Optional`, `from typing import List`, `from typing import Dict`, `class Config:`, `.dict()`, `.json()` in incident_agent/.\n4. RULE-CODE-05: grep for `random.seed(` in incident_agent/ and tests/.\n5. RULE-CODE-07: grep api.py for module-level `IncidentMemory()`, `CascadeFlowRouter()`, `CostCurveTracker()`, `IncidentWorkflow(...)` singletons. Per-request instantiation is non-compliant.\n6. RULE-CODE-10: grep for hard-coded model strings `qwen/qwen3-32b`, `openai/gpt-oss-120b`, `api.hindsight.vectorize.io` outside `.env.example` and config tables.\n7. RULE-TRIAGE-01..05: confirm tests/property/test_triage.py and test_workflow.py cover P11, P12, P15.\n8. RULE-MEMORY-01: grep for `client.recall` and `client.retain` calls; each must be inside a try/except that calls `_flip_to_fallback` on failure.\n9. RULE-COST-01..02: confirm CostCurveTracker.record is called for every analyzed alert and that bypass alerts pass cost_usd=0.0.\n10. RULE-SEC-01..06: run `scripts/smoke_test.py smoke_env_example` and report. grep tracked files for `gsk_[A-Za-z0-9_]{20,}` and `hsk_[A-Za-z0-9_]{20,}` (excluding .env which is gitignored). Confirm .gitignore includes .env, data/local_memory.json, data/decision_cache.json.\n11. RULE-TEST-01..06: confirm OPENRECALL_PBT_SEED=20260101 in .github/workflows/ci.yml. Confirm every test docstring under tests/property/ carries `Feature: openrecall, Property N:` tag.\n12. RULE-GIT: confirm current branch is not main/master.\n13. RULE-UI-01..06: confirm frontend/src/components/ui/v0-ai-chat.tsx exists, `DecisionBadge` palette covers every TriageDecision Literal value, every triage-card subsection uses the `Section` wrapper, and no `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` env var holds an API key.\n14. RULE-KIRO-01: confirm no .kiro.hook, SKILL.md, or steering file lives inside incident-memory-agent/.\n\nFor each FAIL, cite the rule ID, the file/line, and the suggested fix. Conclude with a one-line summary: `Rules audit: <PASS_count>/<TOTAL> passed.`"
  }
}
